    "voiceover_text": "The design process with Zara was amazing. We spent time in Spain cultivating a collection that feels very much Willy Chavarria, but also has its own unique perspective. My name is Rebeca Mendoza and I'm the head of design for Willy Chavarria. I think when we started thinking about the collaboration, what we were thinking about was what would Willy Chavarria fans want to be able to purchase from this collection. I absolutely love what Rebeca is wearing today. It's got an amazing strong shoulder and it's just really chic. One of my favorite pieces is a blouse that has floral print. The rose to me represents love, passion, and intimacy. There's so much of the essence of our brand in the collection. It's very much what we see on the runway, but it's interpreted for a much wider global audience.",
